               <head>Commentary on the Fakhr al-Hasan</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Sharḥ-i Fakhr-i Ḥasan by Kalīm Allāh ibn Ṣibghat Allāh</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008111616 https://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008121357" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_974A-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f7206">Kalīm Allāh ibn Ṣibghat Allāh</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="person_f7206">كليم الله ابن صبغة الله </persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21806">Sharḥ-i Fakhr-i Ḥasan</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21806">شرح فخر حسن</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Persian translation and commentary by <persName key="person_f7206" role="aut">Kalīm Allāh ibn Ṣibghat Allāh</persName> on the <title>Fakhr al-Ḥasan</title> of <persName key="person_f7482" role="ant">Muḥammad Fakhr al-Dīn ibn Qāz̤ī Munʿim Niẓām al-Dīn Niẓāmī Awrangābādī Dihlavī</persName> (d. 27 Jumādá II 1199/7 May 1785), a work on the authenticity of the chain of transmission or isnād of traditions from the <persName key="person_34436377" role="subject">Imam and Caliph ʿAlī</persName> to <persName key="person_90045570" role="subject">Ḥasan of Baṣrah</persName> without further intermediary links. 

                        </p>
                        <p>The work is divided into four bāb. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated. 
</p>
                        <p>Tooled leather binding with central medallion and corner quarter-medallions; damaged. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
